# Part 1. Overall Architecture

---

# 1. Purpose

## Responsibility

Define the implementation architecture of the XML Generation System.

This document serves as the implementation blueprint for developers.

Unlike previous design documents, this document focuses on software components, dependencies, and responsibilities rather than business requirements.

---

## Objectives

* Define implementation layers.
* Define package organization.
* Define dependency rules.
* Define responsibilities of each package.
* Provide the foundation for implementation.

---

# 2. Architecture Style

## Architecture

The application adopts a layered architecture.

```text
Presentation Layer
        │
        ▼
Application Layer
        │
        ▼
Domain Layer
        │
        ▼
Infrastructure Layer
```

Business logic shall always reside inside the Application Layer or Domain Layer.

Controllers and Repositories shall never contain business logic.

---

## Characteristics

* Layered Architecture
* Stateless Application Services
* Repository Pattern
* Builder Pattern
* Factory Pattern
* Dependency Injection
* Single Responsibility Principle

---

