# 4. Layer Responsibilities

## Presentation Layer

### Responsibility

Handle HTTP communication.

### Owns

* Controllers
* DTOs

### Allowed Dependencies

```text
Controller

↓

Service
```

### Forbidden

```text
Controller

↓

Repository
```

```text
Controller

↓

Database
```

---

## Application Layer

### Responsibility

Coordinate business use cases.

### Owns

* Services

### Responsibilities

* Execute business workflows.
* Manage transactions.
* Invoke repositories.
* Invoke XML Engine.

### Allowed Dependencies

```text
Service

↓

Repository

Service

↓

Engine
```

---

## Domain Layer

### Responsibility

Contain business models and XML Generation Engine.

### Owns

* Entities
* Validators
* Builders
* Runtime Models
* XML Engine

The Domain Layer shall not depend on HTTP or database implementation details.

---

## Infrastructure Layer

### Responsibility

Interact with external systems.

### Owns

* Repositories
* Configurations
* Utilities

Infrastructure components shall not contain business rules.

