# 6. Runtime Communication

## Standard Flow

```text
HTTP Request

↓

Controller

↓

Service

├────────────► Repository

└────────────► XML Engine

                    │

                    ▼

           Validation Engine

                    │

                    ▼

             XML Builder

                    │

                    ▼

          Export Processor

↓

Repository

↓

Controller

↓

Global Exception Handler

↓

HTTP Response
```

---

## Exception Handling

The Presentation Layer shall provide a centralized exception handling mechanism.

Examples include:

* Controller Advice
* Exception Middleware
* Global Error Handler

Responsibilities include:

* Catch unhandled exceptions.
* Convert exceptions into standardized HTTP responses.
* Return the Error Codes defined in `06-api-design.md`.
* Prevent internal implementation details from being exposed to clients.

Business components shall throw domain-specific exceptions.

Presentation components are responsible for translating them into HTTP responses.

---

## Notes

Every request shall pass through the Service layer.

Controllers never communicate directly with Repositories.

Repositories never invoke business workflows.

XML Engine components shall not generate HTTP responses or interact with transport-specific exception handling.


